# OpticalConstructor

## Purpose

Gates that exercise the Optical Constructor application built on top
of the Berreman solver — the five new F# projects spec 0022 §A.1
adds under `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/`
(`OpticalConstructor.Domain`, `.Storage`, `.Optimization`, `.Ui`,
`.App`). Unlike the `Berreman` group (which is scoped to the pure
numerical optics solver and its sibling library projects), this
group covers the orchestration/app layer: the net-new beam-tree
topology, the JSON-canonical storage + schema validation, the
library-agnostic optimization interface, the units spine, and the
Avalonia/FuncUI UI. Per spec §A.6/P3 the model/`update` logic
contains no Avalonia type, so the Domain/Storage/Optimization
behaviour is testable without a UI — gates here target that UI-less
test surface first. Build runs via `dotnet build` of the whole
`Berreman.slnx` (the root `build` gate already covers the new
projects, since they are added to the solution); tests run via
`dotnet test`.

## When to add a gate here

Add a gate here when the new check exercises one of the
`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/**` projects rather than the pure
solver — for example a `dotnet test` over the constructor's UI-less
test project(s), an integration check over the beam-tree
orchestration, or a JSON-schema validation gate. Use a descriptive
stem; gate names are unique across the whole `.gates/` tree, so
prefix constructor test gates (e.g. `constructor-unit-tests`) to
avoid colliding with the `Berreman` group's `unit-tests`. Checks
that exercise the pure Berreman solver or its sibling library
projects belong in the `Berreman` group instead.
